{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"tool_dfKfNXOQqihOTG25dUq5jnRT","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→schema: aidd.spec.v1\n     3→\n     4→# Core\n     5→status: draft\n     6→updated_at: \"2026-03-18\"\n     7→ticket: \"TST-001\"\n     8→slug: \"fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\"\n     9→\n    10→owners:\n    11→  product: \"security-team\"\n    12→  tech: \"backend-lead\"\n    13→  qa: \"qa-lead\"\n    14→\n    15→sources:\n    16→  plan: \"aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\"\n    17→  prd: \"aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\"\n    18→  tasklist: \"aidd/docs/tasklist/TST-001.md\"\n    19→  interview_log: \"aidd/reports/spec/TST-001.interview.jsonl\"\n    20→\n    21→spec_pack:\n    22→  goal: \"Implement live RBAC enforcement on critical APIs, add auditable role operations trail, and synchronize frontend role guards with session updates via WebSocket\"\n    23→  non_goals:\n    24→    - \"UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\"\n    25→    - \"Migration of historical access logs\"\n    26→    - \"Multi-tenant RBAC scope\"\n    27→  constraints:\n    28→    - \"No existing RBAC - build from scratch per interview Q2=D\"\n    29→    - \"WebSocket server must scale with current infrastructure\"\n    30→    - \"Audit logs stored in existing DB (separate table)\"\n    31→    - \"Frontend stack: React + Context/Redux (no changes)\"\n    32→  decisions:\n    33→    - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n    34→    - \"Q2: Current RBAC = none exists, build from scratch [Interview: D - overrides PRD assumption]\"\n    35→    - \"Q3: Frontend = React + Context/Redux\"\n    36→    - \"Q4: Audit logs = database (separate table)\"\n    37→    - \"Q5: Session sync = WebSocket (push updates)\"\n    38→  risks_top:\n    39→    - \"Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy with TTL\"\n    40→    - \"Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism\"\n    41→    - \"Audit log storage growth → retention policy and archiving\"\n    42→  links:\n    43→    spec: \"aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\"\n    44→\n    45→iteration_decisions:\n    46→  - iteration_id: \"I1\"\n    47→    scope:\n    48→      - api_contract\n    49→      - data_model\n    50→      - tests\n    51→      - roll_out\n    52→      - observability\n    53→    decisions:\n    54→      - \"Backend RBAC middleware with audit logging (Phase 1)\"\n    55→      - \"WebSocket push notifications infrastructure (Phase 2)\"\n    56→      - \"Frontend WebSocket integration + Redux state sync (Phase 3)\"\n    57→      - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n    58→      - \"Q2: No existing RBAC - build from scratch [Interview: D]\"\n    59→    open_questions: []\n    60→\n    61→platforms:\n    62→  frontend:\n    63→    enabled: true\n    64→    stack_hint: \"React + Context/Redux\"\n    65→  backend:\n    66→    enabled: true\n    67→    stack_hint: \"Build from scratch - no existing RBAC (per interview Q2=D)\"\n    68→  mobile:\n    69→    enabled: false\n    70→    stack_hint: \"\"\n    71→\n    72→user_flows:\n    73→  - id: \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n    74→    actors: [\"admin\", \"target_user\"]\n    75→    entrypoints: [\"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"]\n    76→    steps:\n    77→      - \"Admin calls API to change user role\"\n    78→      - \"RBAC middleware checks admin permissions\"\n    79→      - \"Role updated in DB, operation logged to audit_log\"\n    80→      - \"WebSocket push notification sent to target user\"\n    81→      - \"Frontend updates auth state without refresh\"\n    82→    edge_cases:\n    83→      - \"Insufficient admin permissions → 403 with audit log\"\n    84→      - \"WebSocket unavailable → graceful degradation\"\n    85→  - id: \"flow.unauthorized-access\"\n    86→    actors: [\"user\"]\n    87→    entrypoints: [\"POST/PUT/DELETE APIs\"]\n    88→    steps:\n    89→      - \"User attempts restricted action\"\n    90→      - \"RBAC middleware checks JWT claims\"\n    91→      - \"Access denied → 403 Forbidden\"\n    92→      - \"Attempt logged to audit_log (user_id, endpoint, timestamp, denied)\"\n    93→      - \"Frontend displays permission error\"\n    94→    edge_cases:\n    95→      - \"JWT token expired → 401 (not 403)\"\n    96→  - id: \"flow.live-session-update\"\n    97→    actors: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n    98→    entrypoints: [\"WebSocket connection\"]\n    99→    steps:\n   100→      - \"User active in React app\"\n   101→      - \"Admin revokes role via API\"\n   102→      - \"WebSocket server broadcasts update\"\n   103→      - \"Redux store updates auth state\"\n   104→      - \"UI immediately hides restricted elements\"\n   105→    edge_cases:\n   106→      - \"Connection lost → exponential backoff reconnect\"\n   107→\n   108→ui_ux:\n   109→  screens:\n   110→    - \"Admin role management interface (existing)\"\n   111→    - \"Permission denied error display\"\n   112→  states:\n   113→    loading: [\"WebSocket connection status indicator\"]\n   114→    empty: []\n   115→    error: [\"403 permission denied message\", \"WebSocket connection error\"]\n   116→    partial_success: []\n   117→  accessibility:\n   118→    - \"Error messages must be screen-reader accessible\"\n   119→  i18n:\n   120→    - \"Permission error messages need i18n support\"\n   121→  analytics_events:\n   122→    - \"role_change_denied\"\n   123→    - \"permission_check_failed\"\n   124→\n   125→api_contract:\n   126→  - id: \"ALL POST/PUT/DELETE /*\"\n   127→    auth: \"JWT Bearer\"\n   128→    request:\n   129→      content_type: \"application/json\"\n   130→      body_schema: {}\n   131→    response:\n   132→      success_schema: {}\n   133→      error_codes: [\"403 Forbidden\", \"401 Unauthorized\"]\n   134→      timeouts_ms: 5000\n   135→  - id: \"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"\n   136→    auth: \"JWT Bearer (admin only)\"\n   137→    request:\n   138→      content_type: \"application/json\"\n   139→      body_schema:\n   140→        role: \"string\"\n   141→    response:\n   142→      success_schema:\n   143→        user_id: \"string\"\n   144→        new_role: \"string\"\n   145→        updated_at: \"timestamp\"\n   146→      error_codes: [\"403 Forbidden\", \"404 Not Found\", \"400 Bad Request\"]\n   147→      timeouts_ms: 3000\n   148→  - id: \"WS /ws/session\"\n   149→    auth: \"JWT Bearer (upgrade)\"\n   150→    request:\n   151→      content_type: \"N/A\"\n   152→      body_schema: {}\n   153→    response:\n   154→      success_schema:\n   155→        event: \"role_updated\"\n   156→        payload:\n   157→          user_id: \"string\"\n   158→          new_role: \"string\"\n   159→          timestamp: \"string\"\n   160→      error_codes: [\"401 Unauthorized\"]\n   161→      timeouts_ms: 30000\n   162→\n   163→data_model:\n   164→  entities:\n   165→    - name: \"audit_log\"\n   166→      fields:\n   167→        - \"id: UUID PK\"\n   168→        - \"user_id: UUID FK\"\n   169→        - \"action: ENUM(GRANT, REVOKE, DENIED)\"\n   170→        - \"target_resource: STRING\"\n   171→        - \"role_changes: JSONB\"\n   172→        - \"timestamp: TIMESTAMP\"\n   173→        - \"ip_address: INET\"\n   174→        - \"user_agent: STRING\"\n   175→    - name: \"user_sessions\"\n   176→      fields:\n   177→        - \"user_id: UUID FK\"\n   178→        - \"role: STRING\"\n   179→        - \"permissions: JSONB\"\n   180→        - \"last_updated: TIMESTAMP\"\n   181→  schema_changes:\n   182→    required: true\n   183→    notes: \"New audit_log table required; user_sessions cache table optional for performance\"\n   184→  versioning: \"backward\"\n   185→  idempotency: \"Role updates must be idempotent (same role set = no-op)\"\n   186→\n   187→tradeoffs:\n   188→  - topic: \"RBAC check caching strategy\"\n   189→    options:\n   190→      - name: \"In-memory cache with TTL\"\n   191→        pros: [\"Fast (<10ms)\", \"Simple implementation\"]\n   192→        cons: [\"Stale data risk\", \"Per-node cache\"]\n   193→      - name: \"Redis distributed cache\"\n   194→        pros: [\"Consistent across nodes\", \"Configurable TTL\"]\n   195→        cons: [\"Network latency\", \"Additional infrastructure\"]\n   196→    decision: \"In-memory cache with TTL\"\n   197→    rationale: \"Meet P95 <10ms latency requirement; accept eventual consistency for role changes via WebSocket push\"\n   198→  - topic: \"Session sync mechanism\"\n   199→    options:\n   200→      - name: \"WebSocket push\"\n   201→        pros: [\"Real-time updates\", \"Efficient\"]\n   202→        cons: [\"Connection management complexity\"]\n   203→      - name: \"Short polling\"\n   204→        pros: [\"Simple implementation\", \"No persistent connections\"]\n   205→        cons: [\"Higher latency\", \"Unnecessary load\"]\n   206→    decision: \"WebSocket push\"\n   207→    rationale: \"<5 second sync requirement demands WebSocket; polling would add unnecessary load\"\n   208→\n   209→risks:\n   210→  - risk: \"Performance impact from live RBAC checks on every request\"\n   211→    impact: \"high\"\n   212→    mitigation:\n   213→      - \"In-memory caching with TTL\"\n   214→      - \"Async audit logging\"\n   215→    detection:\n   216→      - \"RBAC latency P95 metrics\"\n   217→      - \"Alert if >10ms\"\n   218→  - risk: \"Session desync between backend and frontend\"\n   219→    impact: \"med\"\n   220→    mitigation:\n   221→      - \"WebSocket with heartbeat\"\n   222→      - \"Fallback to polling\"\n   223→    detection:\n   224→      - \"WebSocket connection metrics\"\n   225→      - \"Role mismatch logs\"\n   226→  - risk: \"Audit log storage growth\"\n   227→    impact: \"med\"\n   228→    mitigation:\n   229→      - \"Retention policy (90 days)\"\n   230→      - \"Archive to cold storage\"\n   231→    detection:\n   232→      - \"Storage usage monitoring\"\n   233→      - \"Growth rate alerts\"\n   234→  - risk: \"WebSocket connection instability\"\n   235→    impact: \"high\"\n   236→    mitigation:\n   237→      - \"Graceful degradation\"\n   238→      - \"Exponential backoff reconnect\"\n   239→    detection:\n   240→      - \"Connection uptime metrics\"\n   241→      - \"Error rate monitoring\"\n   242→\n   243→observability:\n   244→  logs:\n   245→    - \"RBAC check results (allowed/denied)\"\n   246→    - \"Audit log writes\"\n   247→    - \"WebSocket connection events\"\n   248→  metrics:\n   249→    - \"rbac_check_latency_p95\"\n   250→    - \"rbac_check_denied_total\"\n   251→    - \"audit_log_writes_total\"\n   252→    - \"websocket_connections_active\"\n   253→    - \"websocket_events_sent_total\"\n   254→  traces:\n   255→    - \"RBAC decision path\"\n   256→    - \"WebSocket message flow\"\n   257→  dashboards:\n   258→    - \"RBAC Performance Dashboard\"\n   259→    - \"Audit Log Activity\"\n   260→\n   261→roll_out:\n   262→  feature_flags:\n   263→    - name: \"rbac_live_enforcement\"\n   264→      description: \"Enable live RBAC checks on mutation APIs\"\n   265→    - name: \"websocket_session_sync\"\n   266→      description: \"Enable WebSocket session updates\"\n   267→  stages:\n   268→    - \"Phase 1: Backend RBAC middleware + audit logging\"\n   269→    - \"Phase 2: WebSocket infrastructure\"\n   270→    - \"Phase 3: Frontend integration\"\n   271→    - \"Phase 4: E2E testing + performance validation\"\n   272→  rollback:\n   273→    - \"Disable feature flags\"\n   274→    - \"Revert to previous middleware version\"\n   275→\n   276→test_strategy:\n   277→  unit:\n   278→    scope:\n   279→      - \"RBAC middleware logic\"\n   280→      - \"JWT claims parsing\"\n   281→      - \"Audit log formatting\"\n   282→  integration:\n   283→    scope:\n   284→      - \"RBAC middleware + JWT integration\"\n   285→      - \"Audit log database writes\"\n   286→      - \"WebSocket connection handling\"\n   287→  contract:\n   288→    scope:\n   289→      - \"API response schemas\"\n   290→      - \"WebSocket message format\"\n   291→  e2e:\n   292→    scope:\n   293→      - \"Admin role change flow\"\n   294→      - \"Permission denied flow\"\n   295→      - \"Live session update flow\"\n   296→    critical_paths:\n   297→      - \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n   298→      - \"flow.unauthorized-access\"\n   299→      - \"flow.live-session-update\"\n   300→  test_data:\n   301→    fixtures:\n   302→      - \"Admin user with GRANT/REVOKE permissions\"\n   303→      - \"Regular user with limited role\"\n   304→      - \"User with expired JWT\"\n   305→  environments:\n   306→    stage:\n   307→      - \"Integration test environment\"\n   308→      - \"Load test environment\"\n   309→\n   310→open_questions:\n   311→  blocker: []\n   312→  non_blocker:\n   313→    - \"What is the preferred audit log retention period beyond 90 days?\"\n   314→    - \"Should denied access attempts trigger security alerts?\"\n   315→\n   316→done_definition:\n   317→  acceptance_criteria_map:\n   318→    - ac: \"AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for unauthorized users\"\n   319→      test_coverage: \"e2e flow.unauthorized-access\"\n   320→    - ac: \"AC-2: All role operations logged to audit_log\"\n   321→      test_coverage: \"integration audit_log writes\"\n   322→    - ac: \"AC-3: Frontend updates within 5 seconds of backend change\"\n   323→      test_coverage: \"e2e flow.live-session-update\"\n   324→    - ac: \"AC-4: RBAC latency P95 <= 10ms at 1000 RPS\"\n   325→      test_coverage: \"load test validation\"\n   326→  manual_checks:\n   327→    - \"Verify WebSocket graceful degradation when connection lost\"\n   328→    - \"Verify audit logs do not contain sensitive data\"\n   329→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"28cefa57-de91-45f4-bdfe-02fc2843f5ab","uuid":"1c7685b1-eaed-4da9-9bdf-c3e921d94cd1","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/griogrii_riabov/grigorii_projects/ai_advent_challenge_new/aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml","content":"---\nschema: aidd.spec.v1\n\n# Core\nstatus: draft\nupdated_at: \"2026-03-18\"\nticket: \"TST-001\"\nslug: \"fs-rbac-03-live-enforcement\"\n\nowners:\n  product: \"security-team\"\n  tech: \"backend-lead\"\n  qa: \"qa-lead\"\n\nsources:\n  plan: \"aidd/docs/plan/TST-001.md\"\n  prd: \"aidd/docs/prd/TST-001.prd.md\"\n  tasklist: \"aidd/docs/tasklist/TST-001.md\"\n  interview_log: \"aidd/reports/spec/TST-001.interview.jsonl\"\n\nspec_pack:\n  goal: \"Implement live RBAC enforcement on critical APIs, add auditable role operations trail, and synchronize frontend role guards with session updates via WebSocket\"\n  non_goals:\n    - \"UI for role management (assumes existing admin interface)\"\n    - \"Migration of historical access logs\"\n    - \"Multi-tenant RBAC scope\"\n  constraints:\n    - \"No existing RBAC - build from scratch per interview Q2=D\"\n    - \"WebSocket server must scale with current infrastructure\"\n    - \"Audit logs stored in existing DB (separate table)\"\n    - \"Frontend stack: React + Context/Redux (no changes)\"\n  decisions:\n    - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n    - \"Q2: Current RBAC = none exists, build from scratch [Interview: D - overrides PRD assumption]\"\n    - \"Q3: Frontend = React + Context/Redux\"\n    - \"Q4: Audit logs = database (separate table)\"\n    - \"Q5: Session sync = WebSocket (push updates)\"\n  risks_top:\n    - \"Performance impact of live RBAC checks → caching strategy with TTL\"\n    - \"Session desync between backend/frontend → websocket/polling mechanism\"\n    - \"Audit log storage growth → retention policy and archiving\"\n  links:\n    spec: \"aidd/docs/spec/TST-001.spec.yaml\"\n\niteration_decisions:\n  - iteration_id: \"I1\"\n    scope:\n      - api_contract\n      - data_model\n      - tests\n      - roll_out\n      - observability\n    decisions:\n      - \"Backend RBAC middleware with audit logging (Phase 1)\"\n      - \"WebSocket push notifications infrastructure (Phase 2)\"\n      - \"Frontend WebSocket integration + Redux state sync (Phase 3)\"\n      - \"Q1: Critical APIs = all mutation APIs (POST/PUT/DELETE) [Interview: B]\"\n      - \"Q2: No existing RBAC - build from scratch [Interview: D]\"\n    open_questions: []\n\nplatforms:\n  frontend:\n    enabled: true\n    stack_hint: \"React + Context/Redux\"\n  backend:\n    enabled: true\n    stack_hint: \"Build from scratch - no existing RBAC (per interview Q2=D)\"\n  mobile:\n    enabled: false\n    stack_hint: \"\"\n\nuser_flows:\n  - id: \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n    actors: [\"admin\", \"target_user\"]\n    entrypoints: [\"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"]\n    steps:\n      - \"Admin calls API to change user role\"\n      - \"RBAC middleware checks admin permissions\"\n      - \"Role updated in DB, operation logged to audit_log\"\n      - \"WebSocket push notification sent to target user\"\n      - \"Frontend updates auth state without refresh\"\n    edge_cases:\n      - \"Insufficient admin permissions → 403 with audit log\"\n      - \"WebSocket unavailable → graceful degradation\"\n  - id: \"flow.unauthorized-access\"\n    actors: [\"user\"]\n    entrypoints: [\"POST/PUT/DELETE APIs\"]\n    steps:\n      - \"User attempts restricted action\"\n      - \"RBAC middleware checks JWT claims\"\n      - \"Access denied → 403 Forbidden\"\n      - \"Attempt logged to audit_log (user_id, endpoint, timestamp, denied)\"\n      - \"Frontend displays permission error\"\n    edge_cases:\n      - \"JWT token expired → 401 (not 403)\"\n  - id: \"flow.live-session-update\"\n    actors: [\"user\", \"admin\"]\n    entrypoints: [\"WebSocket connection\"]\n    steps:\n      - \"User active in React app\"\n      - \"Admin revokes role via API\"\n      - \"WebSocket server broadcasts update\"\n      - \"Redux store updates auth state\"\n      - \"UI immediately hides restricted elements\"\n    edge_cases:\n      - \"Connection lost → exponential backoff reconnect\"\n\nui_ux:\n  screens:\n    - \"Admin role management interface (existing)\"\n    - \"Permission denied error display\"\n  states:\n    loading: [\"WebSocket connection status indicator\"]\n    empty: []\n    error: [\"403 permission denied message\", \"WebSocket connection error\"]\n    partial_success: []\n  accessibility:\n    - \"Error messages must be screen-reader accessible\"\n  i18n:\n    - \"Permission error messages need i18n support\"\n  analytics_events:\n    - \"role_change_denied\"\n    - \"permission_check_failed\"\n\napi_contract:\n  - id: \"ALL POST/PUT/DELETE /*\"\n    auth: \"JWT Bearer\"\n    request:\n      content_type: \"application/json\"\n      body_schema: {}\n    response:\n      success_schema: {}\n      error_codes: [\"403 Forbidden\", \"401 Unauthorized\"]\n      timeouts_ms: 5000\n  - id: \"PUT /api/users/{id}/role\"\n    auth: \"JWT Bearer (admin only)\"\n    request:\n      content_type: \"application/json\"\n      body_schema:\n        role: \"string\"\n    response:\n      success_schema:\n        user_id: \"string\"\n        new_role: \"string\"\n        updated_at: \"timestamp\"\n      error_codes: [\"403 Forbidden\", \"404 Not Found\", \"400 Bad Request\"]\n      timeouts_ms: 3000\n  - id: \"WS /ws/session\"\n    auth: \"JWT Bearer (upgrade)\"\n    request:\n      content_type: \"N/A\"\n      body_schema: {}\n    response:\n      success_schema:\n        event: \"role_updated\"\n        payload:\n          user_id: \"string\"\n          new_role: \"string\"\n          timestamp: \"string\"\n      error_codes: [\"401 Unauthorized\"]\n      timeouts_ms: 30000\n\ndata_model:\n  entities:\n    - name: \"audit_log\"\n      fields:\n        - \"id: UUID PK\"\n        - \"user_id: UUID FK\"\n        - \"action: ENUM(GRANT, REVOKE, DENIED)\"\n        - \"target_resource: STRING\"\n        - \"role_changes: JSONB\"\n        - \"timestamp: TIMESTAMP\"\n        - \"ip_address: INET\"\n        - \"user_agent: STRING\"\n    - name: \"user_sessions\"\n      fields:\n        - \"user_id: UUID FK\"\n        - \"role: STRING\"\n        - \"permissions: JSONB\"\n        - \"last_updated: TIMESTAMP\"\n  schema_changes:\n    required: true\n    notes: \"New audit_log table required; user_sessions cache table optional for performance\"\n  versioning: \"backward\"\n  idempotency: \"Role updates must be idempotent (same role set = no-op)\"\n\ntradeoffs:\n  - topic: \"RBAC check caching strategy\"\n    options:\n      - name: \"In-memory cache with TTL\"\n        pros: [\"Fast (<10ms)\", \"Simple implementation\"]\n        cons: [\"Stale data risk\", \"Per-node cache\"]\n      - name: \"Redis distributed cache\"\n        pros: [\"Consistent across nodes\", \"Configurable TTL\"]\n        cons: [\"Network latency\", \"Additional infrastructure\"]\n    decision: \"In-memory cache with TTL\"\n    rationale: \"Meet P95 <10ms latency requirement; accept eventual consistency for role changes via WebSocket push\"\n  - topic: \"Session sync mechanism\"\n    options:\n      - name: \"WebSocket push\"\n        pros: [\"Real-time updates\", \"Efficient\"]\n        cons: [\"Connection management complexity\"]\n      - name: \"Short polling\"\n        pros: [\"Simple implementation\", \"No persistent connections\"]\n        cons: [\"Higher latency\", \"Unnecessary load\"]\n    decision: \"WebSocket push\"\n    rationale: \"<5 second sync requirement demands WebSocket; polling would add unnecessary load\"\n\nrisks:\n  - risk: \"Performance impact from live RBAC checks on every request\"\n    impact: \"high\"\n    mitigation:\n      - \"In-memory caching with TTL\"\n      - \"Async audit logging\"\n    detection:\n      - \"RBAC latency P95 metrics\"\n      - \"Alert if >10ms\"\n  - risk: \"Session desync between backend and frontend\"\n    impact: \"med\"\n    mitigation:\n      - \"WebSocket with heartbeat\"\n      - \"Fallback to polling\"\n    detection:\n      - \"WebSocket connection metrics\"\n      - \"Role mismatch logs\"\n  - risk: \"Audit log storage growth\"\n    impact: \"med\"\n    mitigation:\n      - \"Retention policy (90 days)\"\n      - \"Archive to cold storage\"\n    detection:\n      - \"Storage usage monitoring\"\n      - \"Growth rate alerts\"\n  - risk: \"WebSocket connection instability\"\n    impact: \"high\"\n    mitigation:\n      - \"Graceful degradation\"\n      - \"Exponential backoff reconnect\"\n    detection:\n      - \"Connection uptime metrics\"\n      - \"Error rate monitoring\"\n\nobservability:\n  logs:\n    - \"RBAC check results (allowed/denied)\"\n    - \"Audit log writes\"\n    - \"WebSocket connection events\"\n  metrics:\n    - \"rbac_check_latency_p95\"\n    - \"rbac_check_denied_total\"\n    - \"audit_log_writes_total\"\n    - \"websocket_connections_active\"\n    - \"websocket_events_sent_total\"\n  traces:\n    - \"RBAC decision path\"\n    - \"WebSocket message flow\"\n  dashboards:\n    - \"RBAC Performance Dashboard\"\n    - \"Audit Log Activity\"\n\nroll_out:\n  feature_flags:\n    - name: \"rbac_live_enforcement\"\n      description: \"Enable live RBAC checks on mutation APIs\"\n    - name: \"websocket_session_sync\"\n      description: \"Enable WebSocket session updates\"\n  stages:\n    - \"Phase 1: Backend RBAC middleware + audit logging\"\n    - \"Phase 2: WebSocket infrastructure\"\n    - \"Phase 3: Frontend integration\"\n    - \"Phase 4: E2E testing + performance validation\"\n  rollback:\n    - \"Disable feature flags\"\n    - \"Revert to previous middleware version\"\n\ntest_strategy:\n  unit:\n    scope:\n      - \"RBAC middleware logic\"\n      - \"JWT claims parsing\"\n      - \"Audit log formatting\"\n  integration:\n    scope:\n      - \"RBAC middleware + JWT integration\"\n      - \"Audit log database writes\"\n      - \"WebSocket connection handling\"\n  contract:\n    scope:\n      - \"API response schemas\"\n      - \"WebSocket message format\"\n  e2e:\n    scope:\n      - \"Admin role change flow\"\n      - \"Permission denied flow\"\n      - \"Live session update flow\"\n    critical_paths:\n      - \"flow.admin-change-role\"\n      - \"flow.unauthorized-access\"\n      - \"flow.live-session-update\"\n  test_data:\n    fixtures:\n      - \"Admin user with GRANT/REVOKE permissions\"\n      - \"Regular user with limited role\"\n      - \"User with expired JWT\"\n  environments:\n    stage:\n      - \"Integration test environment\"\n      - \"Load test environment\"\n\nopen_questions:\n  blocker: []\n  non_blocker:\n    - \"What is the preferred audit log retention period beyond 90 days?\"\n    - \"Should denied access attempts trigger security alerts?\"\n\ndone_definition:\n  acceptance_criteria_map:\n    - ac: \"AC-1: All POST/PUT/DELETE APIs return 403 for unauthorized users\"\n      test_coverage: \"e2e flow.unauthorized-access\"\n    - ac: \"AC-2: All role operations logged to audit_log\"\n      test_coverage: \"integration audit_log writes\"\n    - ac: \"AC-3: Frontend updates within 5 seconds of backend change\"\n      test_coverage: \"e2e flow.live-session-update\"\n    - ac: \"AC-4: RBAC latency P95 <= 10ms at 1000 RPS\"\n      test_coverage: \"load test validation\"\n  manual_checks:\n    - \"Verify WebSocket graceful degradation when connection lost\"\n    - \"Verify audit logs do not contain sensitive data\"\n","numLines":329,"startLine":1,"totalLines":329}}}
